<TITLE> Laptop fair begins, eyes 5,000 sale </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 20 (bdnews24.com)--A three-day 'Zoom Laptop Fair 2010' started in Dhaka on Wednesday with the organisers hoping to sell around 5,000 notebooks. Citycell chief executive Michael Seymour inaugurated the fair at Bangabandhu International Conference Centre in the afternoon. This is the third laptop fair in Dhaka, said Asif Sarwar, manager of the event organiser of the fair, Maker Communications Business Development. Two laptop fairs have been organised in Chittagong before. bdnews24.com is the online news partner of the fair. "Only 600 laptops were sold when the fair was organised for the first time three years ago. Last year, 3,000 laptops were sold," he said. There are 15 pavilions and 5 stalls displaying top brands and state-of-the-art technologies. Among the brands are Apple, HP, Dell, Acer, Fujitsu, Gigabyte, Asus, Lenovo, Toshiba and Samsung. The sponsors of the fair Zoom, Citycell Wireless Computer Modem has introduced a new offer in the fair. Its connection can be bought at Tk 4,200 and with free talk-time of Tk 600, free 600 SMS and internet security CD ZTE Zoom Ultra Modem for one year. Every participant organisation is offering special sale and bundle offer in the fair. There are printers, modems and other gift offers with every laptop. Acer Aspire netbook is offering the lowest price at Tk 24,800, featuring business technologies. Every organisation has offered netbooks within Tk 30,000, according to salespersons. Ten percent of the revenue from ticket sales will be spent on warm clothes for the poor and 15 percent on the education of street children, said organisers. Bangladesh Computer Association president Mostafa Jabbar was present in the opening ceremony of the fair which will be open from 10am to 8pm. Entry fee Tk 20. bdnew
